docgo

docgo is a lightweight tool that automatically generates missing Go documentation comments for exported structs, functions and packages. It helps keep Go projects properly documented and resolves many golangci-lint warnings related to missing documentation on exported declarations.

Features

* Automatically adds missing documentation comments.
* Processes exported structs and functions.
* Recursively scans all Go source files in a project.
* Preserves existing documentation comments.
* Helps satisfy golangci-lint documentation checks.

Installation

Build and install the tool by running:

```
make
sudo make install
```

Usage

From the root of your Go project, run:

```
docgo
```

docgo will recursively scan the project and add documentation comments to any exported structs, functions and packages that are missing them. Existing comments are never modified.
